@branscha This was merged in before 11.1 was released. It is included in the binaries from https://netbeans.apache.org/download/nb111/nb111.html. 

I just tried creating an ant based platform application using 11.1, packaged it as a Mac OS X Application. The app.conf and the app.sh has the changes from this merge request.

Is your platform application maven based?

@blackleg thank you for your input - yes switching to a single line indeed works (with the drawback, that it makes it unreadable). For now I removed the commit that enables automatic tests through travis again, as the test seem to be unstable (ok for manual use, not so ok for automatic use)

@sdedic @JaroslavTulach  could you please have a look at this? I think most of the changes are straight forward fixes, but this might raise questions:

https://github.com/apache/netbeans/pull/1451/commits/0ae2e4639ae1d842e2a288dacab99491979bf4db

I decided to remove these tests, as I could not find a trace for the license of the source files. While the files for the *doc tests are also not straight copies of the jsdoc files, they are close enough to the files I could find to be believably derived from the GPLed sources. For the removed tests, only files in the netbeans bugzilla could be found, which is IMHO not enough.

It is still failing to find a root reference which, for example, YourKit displays:

